<p>Incorporating <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/chest-dip" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">chest dips</a> into your training routine can help build strength and muscle in the upper body. It is a progression of the bench dip with <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/36293792/#:~:text=The%20bar%20dip%20is%20an%20appropriate%20progression%20from%20the%20bench%20dip%20due%20to%20the%20higher%20peak%20muscle%20activations." target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">higher peak muscle activation</a> to promote greater improvements in strength and hypertrophy.</p>



