<h2 class="wp-block-heading list-start">Anatomy Of The Triceps</h2>



<p>The <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6136322/#:~:text=The%20triceps%20Brachii%20(TB)%20is%20a%20powerful%20extensor%20muscle%20of%20the%20upper%20extremity.1%20It%20has%20been%20described%20as%20a%20single%20muscle%20unit%20with%20three%20heads%20(medial%2C%20lateral%2C%20and%20long%20heads)" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">triceps brachii</a>, or triceps, is a muscle situated at the back of the upper arm. This muscle is crucial for supporting the extension of the elbow joint needed for straightening the arm. It consists of three heads: the long, lateral, and medial heads of the triceps.</p>



<p>All of the heads support arm function in some way. When we pick up a grocery bag, close a door, and change clothes, the triceps brachii establish arm movement. This muscle is crucial for stabilizing the elbow joint and preventing injury, which is why strengthening the muscle is so important.&nbsp;</p>


